---

<SpecLayout
  title="Route Spec — Gatsby → Astro · Portage"
  description="Portage route specification: migrating a Gatsby project to Astro. gatsby-config.js mapping, GraphQL query conversion, Gatsby Image transforms, plugin ecosystem mapping, routes and redirects, edge cases, output schema, and CLI."
  origin="Gatsby"
  status="active"
  lede="A complete crossing for a Gatsby project: MDX and Markdown content, the GraphQL data layer, gatsby-config.js, and plugin patterns mapped to Astro content collections. Gatsby is in maintenance mode — this route gets you to a modern, zero-JS-default build."
  meta={meta}
  toc={toc}
>
  <section class="spec-sec" id="s01">
    <h2><span class="num">01</span>Overview</h2>
    <p>This route carries a Gatsby project into an Astro project by converting its <strong>content layer</strong> into Astro content collections and its <strong>configuration</strong> into an Astro-native setup. Gatsby's source is unusually clean — MDX/Markdown files in <code>src/pages</code> or <code>src/posts</code>, a <code>gatsby-config.js</code> plugin list, and GraphQL page queries — which makes the extraction phase straightforward and the transform phase precise.</p>
    <p>Portage reads the Gatsby project in place: parses <code>gatsby-config.js</code> to understand plugins and source sets, walks the content tree, converts GraphQL page queries into collection schemas, rewrites <code>&lt;Link&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;GatsbyImage&gt;</code> references, and writes a buildable Astro project with a generated content config.</p>
    <div class="note keep">
      <span class="lbl">Moves intact</span>
      <p>MDX/Markdown posts and pages, frontmatter, inline images, GraphQL-sourced metadata, slugs and routes, and gatsby-config plugin mappings. SEO metadata and structured data move into frontmatter.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s02">
    <h2><span class="num">02</span>Extraction</h2>
    <p>Portage treats the existing Gatsby project as the source of truth. No export file needed — it reads the repository directly.</p>
    <h3>A · Project scan</h3>
    <p>Portage locates <code>gatsby-config.js</code> (or <code>.ts</code>, <code>.mjs</code>), parses the plugin array, and identifies content source plugins (<code>gatsby-source-filesystem</code>, <code>gatsby-plugin-mdx</code>, <code>gatsby-transformer-remark</code>, <code>gatsby-source-ghost</code>, etc.). It then walks the configured source directories and collects every <code>.md</code>, <code>.mdx</code>, and <code>.json</code> content file.</p>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">extract · gatsby project</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage extract <span class="fl">--from</span> gatsby <span class="fl">--source</span> . <span class="fl">--to</span> ./astro-project
<span class="out">→ 78 posts · 4 pages · 12 tags · 3 authors · 214 images referenced</span>
<span class="out">→ 8 plugins mapped · 3 GraphQL page queries found</span></pre>
    </div>
    <h3>B · GraphQL query harvest</h3>
    <p>Gatsby page queries live in template files (often <code>src/templates/blog-post.js</code>) or page components. Portage parses the <code>graphql</code> tagged template literals, extracts field selections, and maps them to frontmatter keys and collection schema types.</p>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">extract · query harvest</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage extract <span class="fl">--from</span> gatsby <span class="fl">--queries</span> ./src/templates/*.js <span class="fl">--source</span> . <span class="fl">--to</span> ./astro-project</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <span class="lbl">Note</span>
      <p>GraphQL fragments are inlined and resolved before mapping. If a query references a node type from a source plugin Portage does not yet recognize, the fields are preserved as <code>gatsby:&lt;nodeType&gt;</code> in the manifest for manual review.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s03">
    <h2><span class="num">03</span>Content mapping</h2>
    <p>Each Markdown/MDX file becomes one file in an Astro content collection. Frontmatter passes through directly; GraphQL-sourced fields that were not in frontmatter are injected. Fields not listed are preserved under a <code>gatsby:</code> namespace.</p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Gatsby field</th><th>Source</th><th></th><th>Astro frontmatter</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.title</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">title</span></td><td>Required.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.slug · fields.slug</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx / graphql</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">(filename)</span></td><td>Slug &amp; entry id.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.excerpt · description</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">description</span></td><td>Falls back to generated excerpt.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">(mdx body)</span></td><td><span class="ty">file</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">(body)</span></td><td>Passed through; components rewritten — §04.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.date · publishedDate</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">pubDate</span></td><td>ISO 8601, coerced by zod.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.updated · updatedDate</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">updatedDate</span></td><td>Omitted if equal to pubDate.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.tags[]</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">tags</span></td><td></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.category[]</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">categories</span></td><td></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.author · authors[]</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">authors</span></td><td></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.featuredImage</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">heroImage</span></td><td>Localized — §05.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.imageAlt</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">heroImageAlt</span></td><td></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.seo.title</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">seo.title</span></td><td>Defaults to <code>title</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.seo.description</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">seo.description</span></td><td>Defaults to <code>description</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.canonical_url</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">canonicalURL</span></td><td></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">frontmatter.draft</span></td><td><span class="ty">mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">draft</span></td><td>Boolean or <code>"true"</code> string.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">fields.readingTime</span></td><td><span class="ty">graphql</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">readingTime</span></td><td>From <code>gatsby-transformer-remark</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">fields.timeToRead</span></td><td><span class="ty">graphql</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">timeToRead</span></td><td>Minutes as integer.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s04">
    <h2><span class="num">04</span>Content transforms</h2>
    <p>Gatsby projects often rely on a plugin ecosystem and JSX components inside MDX. Portage maps the most common patterns to Astro equivalents and rewrites imports and JSX usage in the body.</p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Gatsby pattern</th><th></th><th>Astro equivalent</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">&lt;Link to="/path"&gt;</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">&lt;a href="/path"&gt;</span></td><td>Internal links rewritten to anchors.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">&lt;GatsbyImage /&gt;</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">&lt;Image /&gt;</span></td><td>Astro <code>@astrojs/image</code> or native — §05.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">&lt;StaticImage /&gt;</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">&lt;Image /&gt;</span></td><td>Path resolved to <code>src/assets</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-plugin-mdx</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td>Native MDX</td><td>No plugin needed in Astro.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-transformer-remark</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td>Native Markdown</td><td>Remark plugins mapped where equivalents exist.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-remark-images</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td>Astro image pipeline</td><td>Blur-up placeholders become Astro blur-up.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-remark-prismjs</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td>Shiki / Expressive Code</td><td>Syntax highlighting rebuilt in Astro config.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-remark-autolink-headers</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">rehype-slug</span></td><td>Auto-generated heading ids.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-plugin-sitemap</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">@astrojs/sitemap</span></td><td>Configured in <code>astro.config.mjs</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-plugin-react-helmet</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td>Astro <code>&lt;head&gt;</code></td><td>SEO moved to layout <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> and frontmatter.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <span class="lbl">Plugin mapping</span>
      <p>Portage maintains a plugin registry that maps <code>gatsby-config.js</code> entries to Astro equivalents. Unrecognized plugins are listed in the manifest with a <code>⚠ manual-review</code> flag so nothing is silently dropped.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s05">
    <h2><span class="num">05</span>Assets</h2>
    <p>Gatsby images arrive from three sources: <code>src/images</code> (imported or referenced in JSX), <code>static/</code> (copied as-is to the build), and remote URLs in frontmatter or Markdown. Portage reconciles all three.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Localized images</strong> — files in <code>src/images</code> or <code>static/images</code> are moved to <code>src/assets/blog/</code> and references rewritten.</li>
      <li><strong>GatsbyImage transforms</strong> — <code>&lt;GatsbyImage image={...} /&gt;</code> JSX is replaced with Astro <code>&lt;Image src={...} /&gt;</code>; <code>gatsbyImageData</code> objects are converted to plain src paths with Astro handling responsive sizes.</li>
      <li><strong>Static folder</strong> — <code>static/</code> contents are copied to <code>public/</code> with the same relative paths.</li>
      <li><strong>Remote images</strong> — URLs in frontmatter or body are downloaded and deduplicated; pass <code>--images localize-external</code> to fetch them.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="note">
      <span class="lbl">Placement</span>
      <p><code>--images assets</code> (default) writes images to <code>src/assets/blog/</code> for full Astro optimization. <code>--images public</code> writes stable URLs to <code>public/images/</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s06">
    <h2><span class="num">06</span>Routes &amp; redirects</h2>
    <p>Gatsby uses a file-system router (<code>src/pages/</code>) plus programmatic routes from <code>gatsby-node.js</code> <code>createPages</code>. Portage maps both to Astro's file-system router and generates dynamic route fallbacks where needed.</p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Gatsby route</th><th></th><th>Astro route</th><th>Handled by</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">src/pages/blog/&lcub;slug&rcub;.js</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">src/pages/blog/&lcub;slug&rcub;.astro</span></td><td>Dynamic route</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">src/pages/about.js</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">src/pages/about.astro</span></td><td>Static page</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">createPages → /&lcub;slug&rcub;/</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">src/pages/&lcub;slug&rcub;.astro</span></td><td>Dynamic route + manifest</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-plugin-feed /rss</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">/rss.xml</span></td><td><code>@astrojs/rss</code> + redirect</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">gatsby-plugin-sitemap</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">/sitemap-index.xml</span></td><td><code>@astrojs/sitemap</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">/tag/&lcub;slug&rcub;/</span></td><td class="arrowcell">→</td><td><span class="af">/tag/&lcub;slug&rcub;/</span></td><td>Generated taxonomy pages</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>createPages mapping</strong> — <code>gatsby-node.js</code> is parsed; <code>createPage</code> calls with <code>path</code> and <code>component</code> are mapped to Astro dynamic routes. The GraphQL <code>query</code> inside <code>createPages</code> becomes the collection loader.</li>
      <li><strong>Trailing slashes</strong> — Gatsby often uses trailing slashes; Portage sets <code>trailingSlash: 'always'</code> in <code>astro.config.mjs</code> to preserve SEO equity.</li>
      <li><strong>Redirect map</strong> — any route shape changes (e.g. <code>/blog/post/&lcub;slug&rcub;</code> → <code>/blog/&lcub;slug&rcub;/</code>) emit a redirect entry.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s07">
    <h2><span class="num">07</span>Out of scope</h2>
    <p>Gatsby is a React framework with a deep plugin ecosystem. Not every pattern has an Astro equivalent, and Portage tells you explicitly what it skipped rather than failing silently.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Client-only routes</strong> — <code>@reach/router</code> client-side routes (e.g. <code>/app/*</code>) are not converted; they need to be rebuilt as Astro islands or moved to a separate app.</li>
      <li><strong>gatsby-browser.js / gatsby-ssr.js</strong> — browser/SSR wrap logic is carried as comments in <code>astro.config.mjs</code> for reference, but Astro's hydration model is different.</li>
      <li><strong>Custom webpack config</strong> — not transferable; Astro uses Vite. Alias mappings are migrated where possible.</li>
      <li><strong>gatsby-image art direction</strong> — complex <code>artDirection</code> arrays are simplified to a single responsive image.</li>
      <li><strong>Serverless functions (Gatsby Functions)</strong> — <code>src/api/*</code> is not converted; migrate to Astro endpoints or a separate API.</li>
      <li><strong>Theme UI / styled-components context</strong> — CSS-in-JS runtime theming is not migrated; tokens are extracted as CSS custom properties where detectable.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="note warn">
      <span class="lbl">Client routes</span>
      <p>Any <code>matchPath</code> entries in <code>createPages</code> are flagged in the manifest as <code>client-only</code>. These routes will 404 in a static Astro build until you add a dynamic route or move them to an island architecture.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s08">
    <h2><span class="num">08</span>Edge cases</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>GraphQL fragments across files</strong> — fragments imported via <code>...FragmentName</code> are inlined during query harvest. Missing fragments are reported, not guessed.</li>
      <li><strong>gatsby-node.js with complex logic</strong> — <code>createPages</code> with conditional paths, pagination, or custom context is parsed heuristically; complex cases are flagged for manual review.</li>
      <li><strong>Shadowed theme components</strong> — <code>src/&lt;theme-name&gt;/</code> shadow paths are listed in the manifest; you rebuild them as Astro components.</li>
      <li><strong>gatsby-config as function</strong> — <code>module.exports = ({ env }) => ({ ... })</code> is evaluated with <code>NODE_ENV=production</code> by default; override with <code>--gatsby-env development</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Plugin ordering</strong> — Gatsby plugin order matters for transforms (e.g. remark plugins). Portage preserves the order in the mapped Astro config.</li>
      <li><strong>Slug collisions</strong> — a page and a post with the same slug are namespaced by collection; conflicts are reported in the manifest.</li>
      <li><strong>MDX v1 vs v2</strong> — Gatsby may use MDX v1 or v2. Portage normalizes to Astro's native MDX (v2-compatible) and flags deprecated syntax.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s09">
    <h2><span class="num">09</span>Output</h2>
    <p>A predictable, buildable Astro project. The manifest at the root is the full ledger of what was extracted, transformed, and written.</p>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">project tree</span><span class="meta">output</span></div>
      <pre is:raw>astro-project/
├── src/
│   ├── content/
│   │   ├── blog/             <span class="c">← 78 posts</span>
│   │   └── pages/            <span class="c">← 4 pages</span>
│   ├── assets/blog/          <span class="c">← 198 localized images</span>
│   ├── components/portage/   <span class="c">← MDX component stubs (if --content mdx)</span>
│   ├── pages/
│   │   ├── blog/
│   │   │   └── &lcub;slug&rcub;.astro     <span class="c">← dynamic route from createPages</span>
│   │   └── about.astro       <span class="c">← migrated static page shell</span>
│   └── content.config.ts
├── public/
│   └── images/               <span class="c">← copied from static/ (if --images public)</span>
├── public/_redirects        <span class="c">← 6 generated redirects</span>
├── portage.manifest.json    <span class="c">← extract / transform / load ledger</span>
└── astro.config.mjs         <span class="c">← trailingSlash · sitemap · redirects</span></pre>
    </div>
    <h3>Content collection schema</h3>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">src/content.config.ts</span><span class="meta">typescript</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="k">import</span> { defineCollection, z } <span class="k">from</span> <span class="s">'astro:content'</span>;
<span class="k">import</span> { glob } <span class="k">from</span> <span class="s">'astro/loaders'</span>;

<span class="k">const</span> blog = defineCollection({
  loader: glob({ pattern: <span class="s">'**/*.{md,mdx}'</span>, base: <span class="s">'./src/content/blog'</span> }),
  schema: ({ image }) => z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    description: z.string().optional(),
    pubDate: z.coerce.date(),
    updatedDate: z.coerce.date().optional(),
    heroImage: image().optional(),
    heroImageAlt: z.string().optional(),
    tags: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    categories: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    authors: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    draft: z.boolean().default(false),
    canonicalURL: z.string().url().optional(),
    readingTime: z.number().optional(),
    seo: z.object({ title: z.string().optional(), description: z.string().optional() }).optional(),
  }),
});

<span class="k">export const</span> collections = { blog };</pre>
    </div>
    <h3>Sample migrated post</h3>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">src/content/blog/leaving-gatsby.md</span><span class="meta">markdown</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="t">---</span>
<span class="k">title:</span> <span class="s">"Leaving Gatsby Behind"</span>
<span class="k">description:</span> <span class="s">"Why we moved from a React SSG to Astro's zero-JS default."</span>
<span class="k">pubDate:</span> 2024-09-12
<span class="k">updatedDate:</span> 2025-03-01
<span class="k">heroImage:</span> ../../assets/blog/leaving-gatsby.jpg
<span class="k">heroImageAlt:</span> <span class="s">"A ship leaving a sheltered harbor"</span>
<span class="k">tags:</span> [<span class="s">"migration"</span>, <span class="s">"astro"</span>, <span class="s">"performance"</span>]
<span class="k">authors:</span> [<span class="s">"Dana Reyes"</span>]
<span class="k">readingTime:</span> 6
<span class="k">canonicalURL:</span> <span class="s">"https://blog.example.com/leaving-gatsby/"</span>
<span class="k">draft:</span> false
<span class="t">---</span>

The build times were the first signal. Then the plugin deprecation notices…</pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s10">
    <h2><span class="num">10</span>CLI</h2>
    <p>Three stages, run in order. Each is idempotent and writes to the manifest.</p>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">portage · gatsby → astro</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage extract <span class="fl">--from</span> gatsby <span class="fl">--source</span> ./my-gatsby-site <span class="fl">--to</span> ./astro-project
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage transform <span class="fl">--schema</span> content-collections <span class="fl">--content</span> mdx
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage load <span class="fl">--images</span> assets <span class="fl">--redirects</span> netlify</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Values</th><th>Default</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--from</span></td><td><span class="ty">platform</span></td><td><span class="ty">required</span></td><td>Source platform (gatsby).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--source</span></td><td><span class="ty">path</span></td><td><span class="ty">.</span></td><td>Gatsby project directory.</td></tr>
